an in next life. One may not enjoy that wealth and=\r\n pray whole life for health. In the life after that, one may be very health=\r\ny, but not have any knowledge or money. In another \n&gt;&gt; case, one may deeply=\r\n desire to act in a famous film. One may be reborn \n&gt;&gt; as a tiger or a dog =\r\nand act in a famous film, but not really enjoy that \n&gt;&gt; experience. Basical=\r\nly, people keep going in circles through various lives, always &quot;seeking&quot; so=\r\nmething they are &quot;missing&quot;.\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Anyway, coming back to Kundali=\r\nni, if one deeply desires an out of body experience given by a rising Kunda=\r\nlini and one&#39;s previous karmas constrain one from having it in THIS life, o=\r\nne may be born in next life with this specific desire destined to fructify =\r\n(if there is enough karmik force behind it).\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0\n=\r\n&gt;&gt;  *\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Kundalini rise is not necessarily scary or painful, =\r\nif one is well-prepared in terms of attitude and detachment.\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;=\r\n &gt;&gt;Once I saw a chipmunk glued to a mouse trap. I went to free it and it pa=\r\nnicked so badly and started to shake violently. I went to save it from a ce=\r\nrtain slow death and it was scared that I would kill it!\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;W=\r\ne are like that chipmunk, glued to the mouse trap called this body-mind com=\r\nplex and scared of being rescued from a certain slow death!\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; =\r\n&gt;&gt;If our ideas about who we are (viz this current body-mind complex) are in=\r\ncorrect and if we are this &quot;infinite Self&quot; as shastras say, won&#39;t a complet=\r\ne realization of that at some stage involve stepping out of this body-mind =\r\ncomplex, without being scared?\n&gt;&gt; &g